<h1>Online Bible: New World Translation of the Holy Scriptures</h1>
</noscript>
<p class="title">2 Chronicles 9:1-31</p>
<form class="formtext">
<input type="hidden" name="chapterCount" value="36">
<input type="hidden" name="verseCount" value="31">
<p><a name="bk1" class="vsAnchor">1</a>
       <span id="vs1">And the queen of She&acute;ba herself heard the report about Sol&acute;o&middot;mon, and she proceeded to come to test Sol&acute;o&middot;mon with perplexing questions at Jerusalem, along with a very impressive train and camels carrying balsam oil, and gold in great quantity, and precious stones. At length she came in to Sol&acute;o&middot;mon and spoke with him about everything that happened to be close to her heart.</span> <a name="bk2" class="vsAnchor">2</a>
       <span id="vs2">Sol&acute;o&middot;mon, in turn, went on to tell her all her matters, and no matter was hidden from Sol&acute;o&middot;mon that he did not tell her.</span>
</p>

<p><a name="bk3" class="vsAnchor">3</a>
       <span id="vs3">When the queen of She&acute;ba got to see Sol&acute;o&middot;mon’s wisdom and the house that he had built,</span> <a name="bk4" class="vsAnchor">4</a>
       <span id="vs4">and the food of his table and the sitting of his servants and the table service of his waiters and their attire and his drinking service and their attire, and his burnt sacrifices that he regularly offered up at the house of Jehovah, then there proved to be no more spirit in her.</span> <a name="bk5" class="vsAnchor">5</a>
       <span id="vs5">So she said to the king: “True was the word that I heard in my own land about your matters and about your wisdom.</span> <a name="bk6" class="vsAnchor">6</a>
       <span id="vs6">And I did not put faith in their words until I had come that my own eyes might see; and, look! there has not been told me the half of the abundance of your wisdom. You have surpassed the report that I have heard.</span> <a name="bk7" class="vsAnchor">7</a>
       <span id="vs7">Happy are your men, and happy are these servants of yours who are standing before you constantly and listening to your wisdom.</span> <a name="bk8" class="vsAnchor">8</a>
       <span id="vs8">May Jehovah your God come to be blessed, who has taken delight in you by putting you upon his throne as king for Jehovah your God; because your God loved Israel, to make it stand to time indefinite, so that he put you over them as king to execute judicial decision and righteousness.”</span>
</p>

<p><a name="bk9" class="vsAnchor">9</a>
       <span id="vs9">Then she gave the king a hundred and twenty talents of gold, and balsam oil in very great quantity, and precious stones; and there had not come to be the like of that balsam oil which the queen of She&acute;ba gave to King Sol&acute;o&middot;mon.</span>
</p>

<p><a name="bk10" class="vsAnchor">10</a>
       <span id="vs10">And, besides, the servants of Hi&acute;ram and the servants of Sol&acute;o&middot;mon who brought gold from O&acute;phir brought timbers of algum trees and precious stones.</span> <a name="bk11" class="vsAnchor">11</a>
       <span id="vs11">And the king proceeded to make out of the timbers of the algum trees stairs for the house of Jehovah and for the king’s house and also harps and stringed instruments for the singers, and the like of them had never been seen before in the land of Judah.</span>
</p>

<p><a name="bk12" class="vsAnchor">12</a>
       <span id="vs12">And King Sol&acute;o&middot;mon himself gave the queen of She&acute;ba all her delight for which she had asked, besides [the value of] what she brought to the king. So she turned about and went to her own land, she together with her servants.</span>
</p>

<p><a name="bk13" class="vsAnchor">13</a>
       <span id="vs13">And the weight of the gold that came to Sol&acute;o&middot;mon in one year amounted to six hundred and sixty-six talents of gold,</span> <a name="bk14" class="vsAnchor">14</a>
       <span id="vs14">aside from the men of travel and the merchants who were bringing in and all the kings of the Arabs and the governors of the land who were bringing in gold and silver to Sol&acute;o&middot;mon.</span>
</p>

<p><a name="bk15" class="vsAnchor">15</a>
       <span id="vs15">And King Sol&acute;o&middot;mon went on to make two hundred large shields of alloyed gold (six hundred [shekels] of alloyed gold he proceeded to lay upon each large shield),</span> <a name="bk16" class="vsAnchor">16</a>
       <span id="vs16">and three hundred bucklers of alloyed gold (three mi&acute;nas of gold he proceeded to lay upon each buckler). Then the king put them in the House of the Forest of Leb&acute;a&middot;non.</span>
</p>

<p><a name="bk17" class="vsAnchor">17</a>
       <span id="vs17">Further, the king made a great ivory throne and overlaid it with pure gold.</span> <a name="bk18" class="vsAnchor">18</a>
       <span id="vs18">And there were six steps to the throne, and there was a footstool in gold to the throne (they were attached), and there were armrests on this side and on that side by the place of sitting, and two lions were standing beside the armrests.</span> <a name="bk19" class="vsAnchor">19</a>
       <span id="vs19">And there were twelve lions standing there upon the six steps on this side and on that side. No other kingdom had any made just like it.</span> <a name="bk20" class="vsAnchor">20</a>
       <span id="vs20">And all the drinking vessels of King Sol&acute;o&middot;mon were of gold, and all the vessels of the House of the Forest of Leb&acute;a&middot;non were of pure gold. There was nothing of silver; it was considered as nothing at all in the days of Sol&acute;o&middot;mon.</span> <a name="bk21" class="vsAnchor">21</a>
       <span id="vs21">For ships belonging to the king were going to Tar&acute;shish with the servants of Hi&acute;ram. Once every three years ships of Tar&acute;shish would come in, carrying gold and silver, ivory, and apes and peacocks.</span>
</p>

<p><a name="bk22" class="vsAnchor">22</a>
       <span id="vs22">So King Sol&acute;o&middot;mon was greater than all the other kings of the earth in riches and wisdom.</span> <a name="bk23" class="vsAnchor">23</a>
       <span id="vs23">And all the kings of the earth were seeking the face of Sol&acute;o&middot;mon to hear his wisdom, which the [true] God had put in his heart.</span> <a name="bk24" class="vsAnchor">24</a>
       <span id="vs24">And they were bringing each his gift, articles of silver and articles of gold and garments, armor and balsam oil, horses and mules as a yearly matter of course.</span> <a name="bk25" class="vsAnchor">25</a>
       <span id="vs25">And Sol&acute;o&middot;mon came to have four thousand stalls of horses and chariots and twelve thousand steeds, and he kept them stationed in the chariot cities and close by the king in Jerusalem.</span> <a name="bk26" class="vsAnchor">26</a>
       <span id="vs26">And he came to be ruler over all the kings from the River down to the land of the Phi&middot;lis&acute;tines and down to the boundary of Egypt.</span> <a name="bk27" class="vsAnchor">27</a>
       <span id="vs27">Furthermore, the king made the silver in Jerusalem like the stones; and cedarwood he made like the sycamore trees that are in the She&middot;phe&acute;lah for abundance.</span> <a name="bk28" class="vsAnchor">28</a>
       <span id="vs28">And there were those bringing out horses to Sol&acute;o&middot;mon from Egypt and from all the other lands.</span>
</p>

<p><a name="bk29" class="vsAnchor">29</a>
       <span id="vs29">As for the rest of the affairs of Sol&acute;o&middot;mon, the first and the last, are they not written among the words of Nathan the prophet and in the prophecy of A&middot;hi&acute;jah the Shi&acute;lo&middot;nite and in the record of visions of Id&acute;do the visionary concerning Jer&middot;o&middot;bo&acute;am the son of Ne&acute;bat?</span> <a name="bk30" class="vsAnchor">30</a>
       <span id="vs30">And Sol&acute;o&middot;mon continued to reign in Jerusalem over all Israel for forty years.</span> <a name="bk31" class="vsAnchor">31</a>
       <span id="vs31">Finally Sol&acute;o&middot;mon lay down with his forefathers. So they buried him in the City of David his father; and Re&middot;ho&middot;bo&acute;am his son began to reign in place of him.</span>
</p>
</form>

