<h1>Online Bible: New World Translation of the Holy Scriptures</h1>
</noscript>
<p class="title">2 Chronicles 11:1-23</p>
<form class="formtext">
<input type="hidden" name="chapterCount" value="36">
<input type="hidden" name="verseCount" value="23">
<p><a name="bk1" class="vsAnchor">1</a>
       <span id="vs1">When Re&middot;ho&middot;bo&acute;am arrived at Jerusalem, he immediately congregated the house of Judah and Benjamin, a hundred and eighty thousand choice men able-bodied for war, to fight against Israel so as to bring the kingdom back to Re&middot;ho&middot;bo&acute;am.</span> <a name="bk2" class="vsAnchor">2</a>
       <span id="vs2">Then the word of Jehovah came to She&middot;mai&acute;ah the man of the [true] God, saying:</span> <a name="bk3" class="vsAnchor">3</a>
       <span id="vs3">“Say to Re&middot;ho&middot;bo&acute;am the son of Sol&acute;o&middot;mon the king of Judah and to all Israel in Judah and Benjamin, saying,</span> <a name="bk4" class="vsAnchor">4</a>
       <span id="vs4">‘This is what Jehovah has said: “Y<span class="smallcaps">OU</span> must not go up and fight against <span class="smallcaps">YOUR</span> brothers. Return each one to his house, for it is at my own instance that this thing has been brought about.”’” So they obeyed the word of Jehovah and returned from going against Jer&middot;o&middot;bo&acute;am.</span>
</p>

<p><a name="bk5" class="vsAnchor">5</a>
       <span id="vs5">And Re&middot;ho&middot;bo&acute;am continued to dwell in Jerusalem and proceeded to build fortified cities in Judah.</span> <a name="bk6" class="vsAnchor">6</a>
       <span id="vs6">Thus he rebuilt Beth&acute;le&middot;hem and E&acute;tam and Te&middot;ko&acute;a,</span> <a name="bk7" class="vsAnchor">7</a>
       <span id="vs7">and Beth-zur and So&acute;co and A&middot;dul&acute;lam,</span> <a name="bk8" class="vsAnchor">8</a>
       <span id="vs8">and Gath and Ma&middot;re&acute;shah and Ziph,</span> <a name="bk9" class="vsAnchor">9</a>
       <span id="vs9">and Ad&middot;o&middot;ra&acute;im and La&acute;chish and A&middot;ze&acute;kah,</span> <a name="bk10" class="vsAnchor">10</a>
       <span id="vs10">and Zo&acute;rah and Ai&acute;ja&middot;lon and He&acute;bron, fortified cities, which were in Judah and Benjamin.</span> <a name="bk11" class="vsAnchor">11</a>
       <span id="vs11">Further, he reinforced the fortified places and put leaders in them and supplies of food and oil and wine,</span> <a name="bk12" class="vsAnchor">12</a>
       <span id="vs12">and in all the different cities large shields and lances; and he went on reinforcing them to a very great degree. And Judah and Benjamin continued his.</span>
</p>

<p><a name="bk13" class="vsAnchor">13</a>
       <span id="vs13">And the priests and the Levites themselves that were in all Israel took their stand by him out of all their territories.</span> <a name="bk14" class="vsAnchor">14</a>
       <span id="vs14">For the Levites left their pasture grounds and their possession and then came to Judah and Jerusalem, because Jer&middot;o&middot;bo&acute;am and his sons had discharged them from acting as priests to Jehovah.</span> <a name="bk15" class="vsAnchor">15</a>
       <span id="vs15">And he proceeded to put in office for himself priests for the high places and for the goat-shaped demons and for the calves that he had made.</span> <a name="bk16" class="vsAnchor">16</a>
       <span id="vs16">And following them from all the tribes of Israel those that were giving their heart to seek Jehovah the God of Israel came themselves to Jerusalem to sacrifice to Jehovah the God of their forefathers.</span> <a name="bk17" class="vsAnchor">17</a>
       <span id="vs17">And they kept strengthening the kingship of Judah and confirming Re&middot;ho&middot;bo&acute;am the son of Sol&acute;o&middot;mon for three years, for they walked in the way of David and Sol&acute;o&middot;mon for three years.</span>
</p>

<p><a name="bk18" class="vsAnchor">18</a>
       <span id="vs18">Then Re&middot;ho&middot;bo&acute;am took as his wife Ma&acute;ha&middot;lath the daughter of Jer&acute;i&middot;moth the son of David, and of Ab&acute;i&middot;ha&middot;il the daughter of E&middot;li&acute;ab the son of Jes&acute;se.</span> <a name="bk19" class="vsAnchor">19</a>
       <span id="vs19">In time she bore him sons, Je&acute;ush and Shem&middot;a&middot;ri&acute;ah and Za&acute;ham.</span> <a name="bk20" class="vsAnchor">20</a>
       <span id="vs20">And after her he took Ma&acute;a&middot;cah the granddaughter of Ab&acute;sa&middot;lom. In time she bore him A&middot;bi&acute;jah and At&acute;tai and Zi&acute;za and She&middot;lo&acute;mith.</span> <a name="bk21" class="vsAnchor">21</a>
       <span id="vs21">And Re&middot;ho&middot;bo&acute;am was more in love with Ma&acute;a&middot;cah the granddaughter of Ab&acute;sa&middot;lom than all his other wives and his concubines; for there were eighteen wives that he had taken, also sixty concubines, so that he became father to twenty-eight sons and sixty daughters.</span> <a name="bk22" class="vsAnchor">22</a>
       <span id="vs22">Consequently Re&middot;ho&middot;bo&acute;am put A&middot;bi&acute;jah the son of Ma&acute;a&middot;cah in office as head, as leader among his brothers, for [he thought] of making him king.</span> <a name="bk23" class="vsAnchor">23</a>
       <span id="vs23">However, he acted understandingly and distributed some out of all his sons to all the lands of Judah and of Benjamin, to all the fortified cities, and gave them food in abundance and procured a multitude of wives [for them].</span>
</p>
</form>

<script language="JavaScript1.2" type="text/javascript">
