<h1>Online Bible: New World Translation of the Holy Scriptures</h1>
</noscript>
<p class="title">2 Chronicles 20:1-37</p>
<form class="formtext">
<input type="hidden" name="chapterCount" value="36">
<input type="hidden" name="verseCount" value="37">
<p><a name="bk1" class="vsAnchor">1</a>
       <span id="vs1">And it came about afterward that the sons of Mo&acute;ab and the sons of Am&acute;mon and with them some of the Am&acute;mon&middot;im came against Je&middot;hosh&acute;a&middot;phat in war.</span> <a name="bk2" class="vsAnchor">2</a>
       <span id="vs2">So people came and told Je&middot;hosh&acute;a&middot;phat, saying: “There has come against you a large crowd from the region of the sea, from E&acute;dom; and there they are in Haz&acute;a&middot;zon-ta&acute;mar, that is to say, En-ge&acute;di.”</span> <a name="bk3" class="vsAnchor">3</a>
       <span id="vs3">At that Je&middot;hosh&acute;a&middot;phat became afraid and set his face to search for Jehovah. So he proclaimed a fast for all Judah.</span> <a name="bk4" class="vsAnchor">4</a>
       <span id="vs4">Eventually those of Judah were collected together to inquire of Jehovah. Even from all the cities of Judah they came to consult Jehovah.</span>
</p>

<p><a name="bk5" class="vsAnchor">5</a>
       <span id="vs5">Then Je&middot;hosh&acute;a&middot;phat stood up in the congregation of Judah and of Jerusalem in the house of Jehovah before the new courtyard,</span> <a name="bk6" class="vsAnchor">6</a>
       <span id="vs6">and he proceeded to say:</span>
</p>

<p> 
       <span id="vs6-2">“O Jehovah the God of our forefathers, are you not God in the heavens, and are you not dominating over all the kingdoms of the nations, and are there not in your hand power and mightiness, with no one to hold his ground against you?</span> <a name="bk7" class="vsAnchor">7</a>
       <span id="vs7">Did not you yourself, O God of ours, drive away the inhabitants of this land from before your people Israel and then give it to the seed of Abraham, your lover, to time indefinite?</span> <a name="bk8" class="vsAnchor">8</a>
       <span id="vs8">And they took up dwelling in it, and they proceeded to build in it for you a sanctuary for your name, saying,</span> <a name="bk9" class="vsAnchor">9</a>
       <span id="vs9">‘If there should come upon us calamity, sword, adverse judgment, or pestilence or famine, let us stand before this house and before you (for your name is in this house), that we may call to you for aid out of our distress, and may you hear and save.’</span> <a name="bk10" class="vsAnchor">10</a>
       <span id="vs10">And now here the sons of Am&acute;mon, and Mo&acute;ab and the mountainous region of Se&acute;ir, whom you did not allow Israel to invade when they were coming out of the land of Egypt, but they turned away from them and did not annihilate them,</span> <a name="bk11" class="vsAnchor">11</a>
       <span id="vs11">yes, here they are rewarding us by coming in to drive us out from your possession that you caused us to possess.</span> <a name="bk12" class="vsAnchor">12</a>
       <span id="vs12">O our God, will you not execute judgment upon them? For in us there is no power before this large crowd that is coming against us; and we ourselves do not know what we ought to do, but our eyes are toward you.”</span>
</p>

<p><a name="bk13" class="vsAnchor">13</a>
       <span id="vs13">All the while all those of Judah were standing before Jehovah, even their little ones, their wives and their sons.</span>
</p>

<p><a name="bk14" class="vsAnchor">14</a>
       <span id="vs14">Now as for Ja&middot;ha&middot;zi&acute;el the son of Zech&middot;a&middot;ri&acute;ah the son of Be&middot;nai&acute;ah the son of Je&middot;i&acute;el the son of Mat&middot;ta&middot;ni&acute;ah the Levite of the sons of A&acute;saph, the spirit of Jehovah came to be upon him in the middle of the congregation.</span> <a name="bk15" class="vsAnchor">15</a>
       <span id="vs15">Consequently he said: “Pay attention, all Judah and <span class="smallcaps">YOU</span> inhabitants of Jerusalem and King Je&middot;hosh&acute;a&middot;phat! Here is what Jehovah has said to <span class="smallcaps">YOU</span>, ‘Do not <span class="smallcaps">YOU</span> be afraid or be terrified because of this large crowd; for the battle is not <span class="smallcaps">YOURS</span>, but God’s.</span> <a name="bk16" class="vsAnchor">16</a>
       <span id="vs16">Tomorrow go down against them. There they are coming up by the pass of Ziz; and <span class="smallcaps">YOU</span> will be certain to find them at the end of the torrent valley in front of the wilderness of Je&middot;ru&acute;el.</span> <a name="bk17" class="vsAnchor">17</a>
       <span id="vs17">Y<span class="smallcaps">OU</span> will not need to fight in this instance. Take <span class="smallcaps">YOUR</span> position, stand still and see the salvation of Jehovah in <span class="smallcaps">YOUR</span> behalf. O Judah and Jerusalem, do not be afraid or be terrified. Tomorrow go out against them, and Jehovah will be with <span class="smallcaps">YOU</span>.’”</span>
</p>

<p><a name="bk18" class="vsAnchor">18</a>
       <span id="vs18">At once Je&middot;hosh&acute;a&middot;phat bowed low with his face to the earth, and all Judah and the inhabitants of Jerusalem themselves fell down before Jehovah to do obeisance to Jehovah.</span> <a name="bk19" class="vsAnchor">19</a>
       <span id="vs19">Then the Levites of the sons of the Ko&acute;hath&middot;ites and of the sons of the Ko&acute;rah&middot;ites rose up to praise Jehovah the God of Israel with an extraordinarily loud voice.</span>
</p>

<p><a name="bk20" class="vsAnchor">20</a>
       <span id="vs20">And they proceeded to rise early in the morning and go out to the wilderness of Te&middot;ko&acute;a. And as they went out, Je&middot;hosh&acute;a&middot;phat stood up and then said: “Hear me, O Judah and <span class="smallcaps">YOU</span> inhabitants of Jerusalem! Put faith in Jehovah <span class="smallcaps">YOUR</span> God that <span class="smallcaps">YOU</span> may prove yourselves of long duration. Put faith in his prophets and so prove successful.”</span>
</p>

<p><a name="bk21" class="vsAnchor">21</a>
       <span id="vs21">Further, he took counsel with the people and stationed singers to Jehovah and those offering praise in holy adornment as they went out ahead of the armed men, and saying: “G<span class="smallcaps">IVE</span> praise to Jehovah, for to time indefinite is his loving-kindness.”</span>
</p>

<p><a name="bk22" class="vsAnchor">22</a>
       <span id="vs22">And at the time that they started off with the joyful cry and praise, Jehovah set men in ambush against the sons of Am&acute;mon, Mo&acute;ab and the mountainous region of Se&acute;ir who were coming into Judah, and they went smiting one another.</span> <a name="bk23" class="vsAnchor">23</a>
       <span id="vs23">And the sons of Am&acute;mon and Mo&acute;ab proceeded to stand up against the inhabitants of the mountainous region of Se&acute;ir to devote them to destruction and annihilate them; and as soon as they finished with the inhabitants of Se&acute;ir, they helped each one to bring his own fellow to ruin.</span>
</p>

<p><a name="bk24" class="vsAnchor">24</a>
       <span id="vs24">But as for Judah, it came to the watchtower of the wilderness. When they turned their faces toward the crowd, why, there they were, their carcasses fallen to the earth without anyone escaping.</span> <a name="bk25" class="vsAnchor">25</a>
       <span id="vs25">So Je&middot;hosh&acute;a&middot;phat and his people came to plunder the spoil on them, and they got to find among them in abundance both goods and clothing and desirable articles; and they went stripping them off for themselves until they could carry no more. And it came to be three days that they were plundering the spoil, for it was abundant.</span> <a name="bk26" class="vsAnchor">26</a>
       <span id="vs26">And on the fourth day they congregated together at the low plain of Ber&acute;a&middot;cah, for there they blessed Jehovah. That is why they called the name of that place Low Plain of Ber&acute;a&middot;cah—until today.</span>
</p>

<p><a name="bk27" class="vsAnchor">27</a>
       <span id="vs27">Then all the men of Judah and Jerusalem returned, with Je&middot;hosh&acute;a&middot;phat at their head, to return to Jerusalem with rejoicing, for Jehovah had made them rejoice over their enemies.</span> <a name="bk28" class="vsAnchor">28</a>
       <span id="vs28">So they came to Jerusalem with stringed instruments and with harps and with trumpets to the house of Jehovah.</span> <a name="bk29" class="vsAnchor">29</a>
       <span id="vs29">And the dread of God came to be upon all the kingdoms of the lands when they heard that Jehovah had fought against the enemies of Israel.</span> <a name="bk30" class="vsAnchor">30</a>
       <span id="vs30">Thus the royal realm of Je&middot;hosh&acute;a&middot;phat had no disturbance, and his God continued to give him rest all around.</span>
</p>

<p><a name="bk31" class="vsAnchor">31</a>
       <span id="vs31">And Je&middot;hosh&acute;a&middot;phat went on reigning over Judah. Thirty-five years old he was when he began to reign, and for twenty-five years he reigned in Jerusalem. And his mother’s name was A&middot;zu&acute;bah the daughter of Shil&acute;hi.</span> <a name="bk32" class="vsAnchor">32</a>
       <span id="vs32">And he kept walking in the way of his father A&acute;sa, and he did not turn aside from it, by doing what was right in Jehovah’s eyes.</span> <a name="bk33" class="vsAnchor">33</a>
       <span id="vs33">Only the high places themselves did not disappear; and the people themselves had not yet prepared their heart for the God of their forefathers.</span>
</p>

<p><a name="bk34" class="vsAnchor">34</a>
       <span id="vs34">As for the rest of the affairs of Je&middot;hosh&acute;a&middot;phat, the first and the last, there they are written among the words of Je&acute;hu the son of Ha&middot;na&acute;ni, which were inserted in the Book of the Kings of Israel.</span> <a name="bk35" class="vsAnchor">35</a>
       <span id="vs35">And after this Je&middot;hosh&acute;a&middot;phat the king of Judah had partnership with A&middot;ha&middot;zi&acute;ah the king of Israel, who acted wickedly.</span> <a name="bk36" class="vsAnchor">36</a>
       <span id="vs36">So he made him a partner with himself in making ships to go to Tar&acute;shish and they made ships in E&acute;zi&middot;on-ge&acute;ber.</span> <a name="bk37" class="vsAnchor">37</a>
       <span id="vs37">However, E&middot;li&middot;e&acute;zer the son of Dod&middot;av&acute;a&middot;hu of Ma&middot;re&acute;sha spoke prophetically against Je&middot;hosh&acute;a&middot;phat, saying: “Inasmuch as you have had partnership with A&middot;ha&middot;zi&acute;ah, Jehovah will certainly break down your works.” Accordingly the ships were wrecked, and they did not retain strength to go to Tar&acute;shish.</span>
</p>
</form>

