<h1>Online Bible: New World Translation of the Holy Scriptures</h1>
</noscript>
<p class="title">2 Chronicles 27:1-9</p>
<form class="formtext">
<input type="hidden" name="chapterCount" value="36">
<input type="hidden" name="verseCount" value="9">
<p><a name="bk1" class="vsAnchor">1</a>
       <span id="vs1">Twenty-five years old was Jo&acute;tham when he began to reign, and for sixteen years he reigned in Jerusalem. And his mother’s name was Je&middot;ru&acute;shah the daughter of Za&acute;dok.</span> <a name="bk2" class="vsAnchor">2</a>
       <span id="vs2">And he kept doing what was right in Jehovah’s eyes, according to all that Uz&middot;zi&acute;ah his father had done. Only he did not invade the temple of Jehovah. However, the people were yet acting ruinously.</span> <a name="bk3" class="vsAnchor">3</a>
       <span id="vs3">He himself built the upper gate of Jehovah’s house, and on the wall of O&acute;phel he did a great deal of building.</span> <a name="bk4" class="vsAnchor">4</a>
       <span id="vs4">And cities he built in the mountainous region of Judah, and in the woodlands he built fortified places and towers.</span> <a name="bk5" class="vsAnchor">5</a>
       <span id="vs5">And he himself warred against the king of the sons of Am&acute;mon and eventually proved stronger than they were, so that the sons of Am&acute;mon gave him in that year a hundred silver talents and ten thousand cor measures of wheat and ten thousand of barley. This was what the sons of Am&acute;mon paid to him, also in the second year and the third.</span> <a name="bk6" class="vsAnchor">6</a>
       <span id="vs6">So Jo&acute;tham kept strengthening himself, for he prepared his ways before Jehovah his God.</span>
</p>

<p><a name="bk7" class="vsAnchor">7</a>
       <span id="vs7">As for the rest of the affairs of Jo&acute;tham and all his wars and his ways, there they are written in the Book of the Kings of Israel and of Judah.</span> <a name="bk8" class="vsAnchor">8</a>
       <span id="vs8">Twenty-five years old he happened to be when he began to reign, and for sixteen years he reigned in Jerusalem.</span> <a name="bk9" class="vsAnchor">9</a>
       <span id="vs9">Finally Jo&acute;tham lay down with his forefathers, and they buried him in the City of David. And A&acute;haz his son began to reign in place of him.</span>
</p>
</form>

